</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32ADAB5FFFC0F58FFE1F765CD75F682" pageId="14" pageNumber="197" type="activity">
<paragraph id="8B8F893EFFFC0F58FFE1F765CD75F682" blockId="14.[113,1319,1990,2496]" pageId="14" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis id="B944552CFFFC0F58FFE1F765CD28F758" bold="true" box="[113,349,2266,2299]" pageId="14" pageNumber="197">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The Gray-bellied Pouched Mouse is presumed to be nocturnal and terrestrial.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32ADAB5FFFC0F58FFE2F696CDA8F6D3" pageId="14" pageNumber="197" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B8F893EFFFC0F58FFE2F696CDA8F6D3" blockId="14.[113,1319,1990,2496]" pageId="14" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis id="B944552CFFFC0F58FFE2F696CF4CF6E9" bold="true" box="[114,825,2345,2378]" pageId="14" pageNumber="197">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
The Gray-bellied Pouched Mouse is presumed to be solitary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
